1553RT Enable
CONFIG_1553_RT_EN
  Say Y here to enable a 1553 Remote Terminal

RT Address
CONFIG_1553_RTADDR
  Enter a remote terminal address between 0 and 31 
  (0-30 if broadcasts enabled).

RT Address parity bit
CONFIG_1553_RTADDRP
  Enter 0 or 1 so that the remote terminal address and 
  this bit achieves odd parity.

Command word
CONFIG_1553_WRTCMD
  Say Y here to make the RT write the command word to memory.

Status word
CONFIG_1553_WRTTSW
  Say Y here to make the RT write the status word to memory.

Enable irq on bad msg
CONFIG_1553_INTENBBR
  Say Y here to enable RT irqs on bad messages.

Enable broadcasts
CONFIG_1553_BCASTEN
  Say Y here to enable broadcasts (address 31 may not be assigned
  to any RT).

Enable loopback
CONFIG_1553_SA30LOOP
  Say Y here to make RT address 30 loopback

RT clock speed 
CONFIG_1553_RTCLKSPD12
  Choose the RT clock frequency

RT clock speed 
CONFIG_1553_RTCLKSPD16
  Choose the RT clock frequency

RT clock speed 
CONFIG_1553_RTCLKSPD20
  Choose the RT clock frequency

RT clock speed 
CONFIG_1553_RTCLKSPD24
  Choose the RT clock frequency

1553BC Enable
CONFIG_1553_BC_EN
  Say Y here to enable a 1553 Bus Controller

BRM enable
CONFIG_1553_BRM_EN
  Say Y here to make enable on or more BRM cores

Number of BRM cores
CONFIG_1553_NUM
  Choose number of BRM cores (1-2)

Bus standard
CONFIG_1553_BRM_ABSTD
  Say Y here to choose MIL-STD-1553 B compliance

BRM Mode
CONFIG_1553_BRM_MS
  Choose operating mode (BC = Bus Controller, RT = Remote terminal, 
  MON = Bus Monitor, RT/MON = Remote terminal and bus monitor
